content:
Talked myself up from a near downward spiral today after hearing my spouse say to their parent something unappreciative of me after not paying attention to my efforts in the area of said complaint.

the breakthru was being able to tell myself that my spouse had not perceived me completing certain tasks. And that it was a misunderstanding. and that i did a good thing.

because i felt myself going into the mindset of feeling unappreciated and targeted, which threatened to light up my feelings of wanting to split and live by myself, and it triggered my regret of not transitioning now (hrt)/deferring.

i disassociated/soothed for about 2 hours , then went exercising and did some intensive skating, which helped me come home feeling really really good.

i think because i spoke calmly and objectively about my feelings after the incident, that my spouse did not get sparked into defensive/deflection mode, and was able to come and give me a sincere apology.

as an #actuallyautistic person I just cannot stand hyperbole, exaggeration, or outright distortion of events. Maybe if I trusted that the person saying these things didnt mean to harm me. My paranoia can be triggered pretty fast sometimes with very specific people.

i do not judge feelings, those are always valid.
